parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS can cause the vehicle to lose braking capability, leading to extended stopping distances, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The ABS warning light illuminates
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal travels to the floor
the vehicle takes longer to stop
or the vehicle experiences a sudden loss of braking power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake pedal can cause the vehicle to lose braking capability, leading to extended stopping distances, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal travels to the floor
or the brake pedal does not return to its normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS hydraulic control unit can cause the vehicle to lose braking capability, leading to extended stopping distances, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The ABS warning light illuminates
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal travels to the floor
or the vehicle experiences a sudden loss of braking power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air suspension system can cause the vehicle to sit lower to the ground, affecting its overall stability and increasing the risk of accidents, particularly when driving at high speeds or navigating rough roads.
symptoms: The vehicle's suspension system fails
causing it to sit lower to the ground
the front or rear suspension drops down to the tires
the vehicle bounces up and down uncontrollably
the vehicle's ride height is uneven
the rear window view is obstructed.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: ABS and Power Assisted Brake System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS and power assisted brake system can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to accidents or near-misses, especially when driving at high speeds or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: The ABS light comes on and stays on
the brake light comes on and stays on
the brake pedal feels tight or hard to press
the vehicle has reduced braking power
the vehicle is unable to stop in a timely manner.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various issues, including faulty fuel indicators, starter failure, and other electrical problems, which can lead to inconvenience, safety risks, and vehicle breakdown.
symptoms: Fuel indicator reads empty on a full tank of gas
starter failure
electrical problems
speed odometer malfunction
car stalling
and brake issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS pump and switch can cause issues with the brake system, leading to safety risks and accidents.
symptoms: Brake issues
car stalling
and speed odometer malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the speed odometer can cause inaccurate speed readings, which can lead to safety risks and accidents.
symptoms: Speed odometer never worked correctly
car stalling
and brake issues.
